Females can be separated from the other species of 

Orestes

by the following combination of characters: all cephalic armature except central coronal present as tubercles (
Fig. 26 I
); tergum IV indistinctly widening towards the posterior, almost parallel-sided (
Fig. 26 A
); metatibiae with dorsal, minute and conical teeth anteriorly and centrally; posteromedial crest on tergum IX not distinctly elongated but notched (
Fig. 26 E–F
).

